This place closes at 10pm. I arrived at 9:24 I was not greeted I was stopped at the entrance with a woman holding the door blocking me from entering saying “do you have a pick up?” I said no we’re here to eat. Then she says uhhhhhhhhh the kitchen closes in 5 minutes. I said ok, can I just use your bathroom (we’ve been on a road trip) I come out and see my husband ordering so we sit down the waitress takes our order then comes right back and says “this is to go right?” At no point did we ask to have it to go then she comes out and says we’re closing. I said, “ what time do you close?” She said 10pm and it was only 9:30. They made us extremely uncomfortable in their establishment and if my husband wasnt desperate for crab boil we would have left like they actually wanted us too. I’m a firm believer that your last customer should be just as important as your first customer. We couldn’t get dessert because “the person who makes it already left” To top it off the crab boil was not the best, not bad but not great. When the waitress explained the reason for the way we were treated she said we only had five customers today so we were trying to close early. In that case, I would think they would have been more grateful for a customer. This might explain why they are lacking customers. The one star is for the smile the one waitress had while she made excuses for why we were treated bad. (Using my husband acct to leave this review)

This place is a solid 4. The lobster roll was incredibly tasty but small and overpriced. My family literally lives in Maine so I have had the best of the best when it comes to lobster rolls, but what made this one special was how different and yet well delivered it was. It had no mayonnaise, just a perfectly toasted roll with butter and claw and tail lobster meat. It was simple but each component was perfectly executed.. the roll was perfect, the amount of butter was perfect, etc. My only complaint would have to be the price and portion size. It should also be noted that I came at an odd time so I was the only one in the place, but I still had to ask for a refill on my soda and had to ask for my check. Still, the waitress was friendly and polite. In that way the service was similar to the food: good (better than most) but not stellar.
